text.tspan: LESSONS-LEARNED REPORT
20 DECEMBER 2020
Project Name: Car Plate Recognition System
Project Sponsor:
AEON Mall
Project Manager:
Quek Yao Jing
Project Dates:
Final Budget:
a.
Did the project meet scope, time and cost goals?
Yes, we did meet the main scope of our project within the time given and successfully complete the task
without the use of extra money and recourses.
b. What was the success criteria listed in the project scope statement?
One of the success criteria set by Aeon is
“detect the car plate successfully and accurately”.
The car plate
needs to be recognised properly so that it can detect the numbers and alphabets on the car plate
accurately.
The criteria of
“plan to complete the project in the time range promised with the buyer”
is also one of the
success criteria listed in the car plate recognition system.
"No additional cost or budget other than those listed”
are also one of the successful criteria listed by QTMT
Inc in this project.
c. Reflect on whether or not you met the project success criteria.
Yes, our system perfectly achieves what we have planned in the initial stage. The system can predict the
scanned car plate correctly and return to the interface. The main successful point is that our system won
the customer’s satisfaction and accepted as we have fulfilled what our system able to do already and have
a completed interface interact with our system. Other than that, the project is finished on time. No extra
funds and cost is needed for this project is required.
d. What were the main lessons your team learned from this project?
The main lesson learned in our project is:
Having good teamwork and communication is the key to success of our project. In our project, every one
of the members have their own role respectively. Each of the member need to overcome the problem
caused by pandemic Covid-19 which some of the members which stay in the red zone cannot come to the
office to work. Hence, we need to
communicate well
to make sure that everyone completed their job to
prevent wasting of time and cost as our project needs to complete in 14 weeks.
To complete the task, Gantt chart is the most important document so that each member can follow the
Gantt chart and complete the milestone according to the time management. However, some portion of
time might be needed to reallocate to cope up with the project delayed.
Moreover, we also learn that risk management needs to conduct in every project. in our project, one of
our members broke his laptop and all the code is missing. After experiencing this problem, we learnt that
risk management is important in our project and we do commit our codes to GitHub every time to prevent
code missing and backup in the cloud repository.
